The paper deals with the trade-off between secret message and secret key rates over a wiretap channel with non-causal channel state information, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also focuses on semantic-security and encryption, which are topics in cryptography (cs.CR). The use of superposition coding and soft-covering lemma suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of coding theory (cs.CC). The paper also deals with the efficient utilization of state sequence, which is a topic in signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper mentions the possibility of applying the derived region to multimedia communication, which suggests that it may also belong to the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
